.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.sp
.LP
If \fIfilename\fR does not exist, \fBreadfile\fR will return  \fBFALSE\fR (that is, the expression will have an error return).
.sp
.LP
\fBlongline\fR returns  \fB0\fR if a \fBreadfile\fR has not previously been issued.
.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
More than one descriptor can call \fBreadfile\fR in the same frame definition file. In text frames, if one of those calls is made from the \fBtext\fR descriptor, then a subsequent use of \fBlongline\fR will always get the longest line of the file read by the \fBreadfile\fR associated with the \fBtext\fR descriptor, even if it was not the most recent use of \fBreadfile\fR.    
